title: For Sale:  Lee Loadmaster w/Accessories, Stand, 223, 9mm, and 45 progressive press
postcontent:
Last month I purchased this (and all of the accessories since then) from Amazon.com.  Decided loading really isn't for me and going to try to recoup some of the money spent.

First, the loadmaster itself is in great condition, I have loaded at most 1,000 rounds with it flawlessly.  I did need to watch some of the video’s to get it tuned in properly, but once it was set it was ready to go.

This was purchased as a 223 kit, and then I bought everything needed to convert it to a 9mm and 45 (Small Rifle, Large Pistol, Small Pistol)

Accessories include everything pictured plus:

Case Collector
Primer Shield
Small Primer Feed
Large Primer Feed
Small Pistol Case Feed
Large Pistol Case Feed
Rifle Case Feed
2 extra turrets
Plates for 9mm, 45, and 223

All in all it’s a fantastic press and I am sad to see it go, I just don’t see the point in having a brand new press in my garage that I will never use.

For the dies I have:
The 223 kit that comes with the press
4 piece 9mm Kit
4 piece 45 kit
Universal decapper die


Basically, everything you need to load small rifle, and all pistol calibers. 

Due to the size and weight I would prefer to do this face to face, I can ship it but I am willing to bet shipping will be up near $50 – 75.  I would also have to dissemble it, and it is set to go right now.

There are 4 small Blemishes total.   I cracked one of the small pistol case feeders, it still works great, just the very end got stuck in the press, and I don’t really pay attention to the right side… crack.   Second, the ramp that the flipper rides on had a bur in it from the factory.  I had to sand it down a bit to make it smooth, overall it is now much better.   The 9mm decaping die has some scratches on the top of it from trying to remove the decapper.  It didn’t come with enough screws, so one of the holders on the bottom is lose and I used those screws to attach the 2nd bin.  Easy enough to switch back if you want it that way, I just find a bin on the left to be very easy.


Price is $325 OBO for everything.
Most of the stuff came from Amazon – I can provide receipts for just about all of it, minus a few things I grabbed from Ebay.

postcontent:
http://extreme-impact-ammo.com/index.php?l=product_detail&p=299

This load is a very high performance +P 45 acp load. The 185gr. hollow cavity Barnes all copper bullet mushrooms readily and still penetrates deeply for such a light bullet, while giving the low recoil and high velocity of a light bullet. This helps fast sight acquisition for quick/accurate follow-up shots. Expect roughly 13 to 14 inches of penetration in flesh and bone.

This load utilizes a low flash powder which gives an important tactical advantage to the shooter as most shootings in the US occur in low light when the criminal element is most active. Being blinded by your own gunfire after the first shot, leaves you very vulnerable.

As usual, Buffalo Bore tests and obtains our advertised velocities from real world over-the-counter firearms. We believe that the industry wide established practice of utilizing extra long test barrels to generate advertised velocities is dishonest and creates expectations that cannot be realized in real guns, in the real world, where it matters. With Buffalo Bore ammo, you’ll actually obtain the velocities we advertise.

1193 fps -- Colt Series 90 Gold Cup, 5 inch
1183 fps -- H&K, USP Tactical, 5 inch
1158 fps -- Glock Model 21, 4.6 inch
1159 fps -- Colt series 80 Commander, 4.25 inch
1110 fps -- Glock model 30, 3.5 inch


In one of the above instances, you’ll note that a longer barrel gave velocities lower than one of the shorter barrels, showing that there is more to internal ballistics, than just barrel length.

This load reliably fed and exhibited very good accuracy in all test pistols.

title: For Sale:  Israeli Military Industries (IMI) Jericho 941FB, 9mm, RARE, excellent!
postcontent:
For sale is an Israeli Military Industries (IMI) Jericho 941FB 9mm pistol. This particular specimen is one of the very early ones that was most likely made for the local Israeli market but ended up being imported by Magnum Research. It maintains it's original name without the typical "Baby Eagle" nomenclature that is now common. It also has the frame mounted safety and appears to have polygonal barrel rifling, both found only on the first ones to come stateside. I believe this one came ashore around 1998. Please note that Armslist only allows me a manufacturer choice of Israeli Weapons Industries (IWI), this pistol was made by Israeli MILITARY Industries (IMI).

The pistol is built like a tank. It's fitted with 3-dot white sights. It's in remarkably good cosmetic condition. The action is super smooth with no slop, the trigger is one of the best factory triggers I've come across. I'm not the original owner so I have no idea of round count, it sure looks like it sat around more than it was fired. Only selling because I'm heavy 9mm handguns right now.

Sale includes pistol with two factory 10 round magazines and the original box.

No trades.

Need to see WDL, CPL/WAC or LE credentials, no exceptions. Thanks for looking.
